    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment team reviewed all 13 V&V 40 factors. Twelve of thirteen factors achieved their required credibility level; the single shortfall (Test conditions, achieved level 1 vs. required level 2) was accepted given the COU scope is limited to static compression-bending and the two-laboratory validation dataset provides sufficient confidence. The output comparison factor demonstrates that all three QoIs satisfy both the <10% difference criterion and the E/uval < 1.96 validation metric. The overall evidence base supports an Accepted decision at Medium assurance level for this Class II device application.",
